    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> I assume that if we have users building their website with React, they might already have a Stats widget on their side which will collide with our own.\n\nWriting copy of the discussion we had with Tim: if we expose our React components in a namespace somewhere at some point like `instansearch.components.Stats` then it should be ok.\n\n@pixelastic If you want to try to trigger a conflict with app.js and a custom Stats + using our Stats widget try it, should be ok. Otherwise close\n",
